stuffs.name: Under cross
stuffs.description: Agroprom, bushes, cross. Tomb under cross.

stuffs.name: Electrical panel in workshop
stuffs.description: The son-of-a-bitch Dehydrator strips us of all our loot. Friggin' old fart. I'm hiding my stuff from his ugly ass inside the electrical panel on the second floor.

stuffs.name: Tractor
stuffs.description: When Timmy fixed the tractor, we got loaded and went for a wild ride at night. Then we ran into a bloodsucker. We had to hightail it real quick, and left our loot-box behind.

stuffs.name: Car in garage
stuffs.description: I stash my junk in the trunk of the commander's 4x4. As long as it ain't going nowhere, my stuff will be safe.

stuffs.name: Case under train car
stuffs.description: Toolbox under train car in Agroprom.

stuffs.name: Bus at the stop
stuffs.description: Toolbox in a bus at the bus stop, near the neutral base.

stuffs.name: Pipe in rubble
stuffs.description: Stash: blocked entrance to the underground, inside an L-shaped pipe.

stuffs.name: Nobody's backpack
stuffs.description: I spotted one on a tree near the Duty base, but had no time to go climbing after it.

stuffs.name: Stalker base
stuffs.description: I tossed my backpack up on that tree crotch, or else everybody would know it was me who did Vitaly in. The shortest way to get there is via the pipes at the neutral base.

stuffs.name: Pipe at the Swamps
stuffs.description: My hideaway is in a pipe at the Swamps. The loot's in the backpack.

stuffs.name: Lost backpack
stuffs.description: We came back from a trip and were resting in the rocks, and somehow I left my backpack. I'll go back and get it when I free up some.

stuffs.name: Rigman's backpack
stuffs.description: I had to climb all the way to the top of that tower until our guys drove those darn dogs away. I had to drop my backpack in the bushes.

stuffs.name: Safe in bushes
stuffs.description: We tried dragging that safe full of junk across the ravine. It was so muddy from the rain that we kept slipping and falling over, and eventually just dropped it along the way.

stuffs.name: Isolated log
stuffs.description: No one's going to come looking for my stash in the log that far out in the sticks.

stuffs.name: Easter eggs
stuffs.description: Come Easter, Tony made us make stashes for the clan. I stuck one of these "Easter eggs" in a log.

stuffs.name: By fence near barbed wire
stuffs.description: OK, I'll pay you with this secret cache - a stalker's backpack that's by a fence. The HV tower will serve as your reference point.

stuffs.name: Under uprooted tree
stuffs.description: We don't have storage rooms in the Zone, sorry! So hurry up and lay your hands on this cache under an uprooted tree before someone else does.

stuffs.name: Corpse in radiation hotspot
stuffs.description: You want great stashes and great stashes is what I got. They'll be yours if you dare go in a radiation hotspot. Your prize lies by the side of a corpse.

item.name: Flash drive with data on balancing the automated parts of a machine gun

stuffs.name: Cylinders on grave
stuffs.description: Honor's worth more than money, so go ahead and take the cache inside some cylinders on an unknown grave.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a machine gun muzzle break

stuffs.name: Corner of fence
stuffs.description: After the last Emission, Valka Squint, God bless his soul, hid something inside this old stump at the corner of a fence.

stuffs.name: Switchboard
stuffs.description: My stash - uhh, sorry, your stash - is inside the switchboard in Duty's base.

stuffs.name: Tree log near tree
stuffs.description: The other day some nice folks told me about a stash that belongs to my enemies. Empty it out, will ya?

item.name: Flash drive with data on pump mechanisms for combat shotguns

stuffs.name: Corpse in van
stuffs.description: These soldiers were speeding their bus so fast they drove right into an anomaly around this area. They all bought the farm, and you just bought their loot.

stuffs.name: Safe under earth slide
stuffs.description: I half-buried a safe with my loot at the bottom of a ravine. Let's pretend it was meant for you all along.

stuffs.name: Confiscated goods near anomaly
stuffs.description: This soldier stumbled into an anomaly, and his backpack with the loot he seized from stalkers is still there, lying next to him. If you're lucky enough, you can make it yours.

stuffs.name: Crate in the basement
stuffs.description: I dumped my stuff in the basement near the doors with the danger sign on them. I have no time right now, but I will definitely get it later.

stuffs.name: Stash in the switchboard room
stuffs.description: I made a nice little stash in the switchboard room, on the second floor of the deserted factory. I'll wait till I have a few more artifacts and then unload them all for some cash.

stuffs.name: Stash at the dead end of the collector
stuffs.description: I accidentally wandered into the dead end of the collector under the base. It looked like a good hiding place, so I stashed away a few goodies in the cross piece of the pipe.

stuffs.name: Stash in the pipe
stuffs.description: I made a stash inside a pipe on the first floor of the deserted factory, near the stairs.

stuffs.name: Pipe under the cistern
stuffs.description: A pack of dogs got on my trail as I was passing by the farm, so I dropped my stuff inside the pipe under the cistern and took off. I'll get it when I can.

stuffs.name: Stash at the factory
stuffs.description: A heck of a stash at the deserted factory. It's right across the entrance, in the cross piece with a valve. It's easy to confuse it with others that look just like it.

stuffs.name: Backpack in the cabin
stuffs.description: I really should go get my backpack from the front seat of the upturned tractor-trailer. I had to dump it the other day, lest I'd get my ass chased down.

stuffs.name: Stash under the fir tree
stuffs.description: I better not forget that particular fir tree where I dumped my loot. The collector entrance is close by, but that still don't make the tree itself stand out.

stuffs.name: Backpack on the tree
stuffs.description: Everybody puts their caches underground, but I made mine on a tree. I bet no one's gonna look there!

stuffs.name: Secret stash under the roof
stuffs.description: I'm not worried about my stash. Even if someone comes looking for it, they'll have to jump across those beams like a squirrel to get to it.

stuffs.name: Stash at the tower
stuffs.description: I told my partner I'd lost my backpack along the way, and the sucker ate it. Actually, I hid it on top of the water tower. It's still there waiting for me.

stuffs.name: Backpack in the elevator
stuffs.description: With all that shooting going on, I had little time to hide my stuff properly. I dumped it in the "hose" under the wooden boards. I'll get it when the time is right.

stuffs.name: Locksmith's case
stuffs.description: I found what used to be a locksmith's case and put my "treasure" inside for a while. I'll move it to a safer cache when I can.

stuffs.name: Safe at the factory
stuffs.description: If someone's reading this, that means I'm six feet under. So, here's what I want you to know about the stash in the safe - I hope you never open it, asshole!

stuffs.name: Safe at farm
stuffs.description: I wasn't sure I'd get out of that scrape alive, so I hid my stuff in this rusty safe at the deserted farm. Now it's time to get it back.

stuffs.name: Tree stump on the island
stuffs.description: A buddy of mine had some real nice goodies on him when he got ambushed in those swamps. He didn't make it, but managed to tell me he hid some of the loot in a rotten tree stump not far from an antenna. I really ought to go get it.

stuffs.name: Rotten tree log
stuffs.description: I don't trust my partner. I think he's gonna try to mug me, so I've been hiding my loot from him. I made a stash near the island bridge, in a tree log. I hope he doesn't find it.

stuffs.name: Rotten tree stump
stuffs.description: I was running from boars the other day and I dumped my things into the hole of a tree stump, not far from the old farm.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near the hill
stuffs.description: I made my stash at the foot of the hill, under an old tree stump. It's a good hiding place - I just hope my luck continues so I can add to it.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near the wooden deck
stuffs.description: I've seen Kolya go near that stump on the island a number of times. I bet the tightwad's got a stash in there. I'll let him collect some more loot before I go check it out.

stuffs.name: Old Zaporozhets car
stuffs.description: The poor bastards are racking their brains, trying to figure out where all their stuff is disappearing! Ha-ha-ha! Well, I've been hiding it in that old little Zaporozhets car near the Swamps. I bet no one's going to look for it there.

stuffs.name: Stash under young fir tree
stuffs.description: Not far from the swamp, I dumped my backpack by a pipe, under a young fir tree.

stuffs.name: Under cistern
stuffs.description: My loot - correction, your loot now - is inside the backpack under the cistern.

stuffs.name: Shrubs near fir tree
stuffs.description: Coming back from a lucky trip, I hid my loot in the shrubs. Now you can make use of it.

stuffs.name: Soldier's corpse
stuffs.description: Write this down: very valuable loot - backpack - hapless military man - right next to an anomaly.

item.name: Flash drive with data on sniper rifle barrels

stuffs.name: Loot in bushes
stuffs.description: I always settle my tabs. And right now my tab is telling me to give you the coordinates of my loot.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a sniper rifle muzzle break

stuffs.name: Safe at Freedom's base
stuffs.description: In the three-story building at Freedom's base there's a safe that holds something valuable for loot-seekers.

stuffs.name: Crate on top of tower
stuffs.description: I appreciate your interest, and will satisfy it with the contents of a blue crate on top of the tower just past Freedom's base.

stuffs.name: Stalker's grave
stuffs.description: You just bought what's under the cross of a stalker's grave next to an old tree.

stuffs.name: Crate under seat
stuffs.description: Under the driver's seat of a red LAZ you'll find a crate. Feel very free to check it out. Or not - up to you.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near fence
stuffs.description: For situations like this one, I've got some junk hidden safely away inside the tree stump that's near a fence.

stuffs.name: Safe in hangar
stuffs.description: I hold true to my words - the promised cache awaits you in a safe at the old factory.

stuffs.name: Corpse near rocks
stuffs.description: You just bought the contents of a backpack that's on the corpse lying near the rocks.

stuffs.name: Safe with weapons and ammo
stuffs.description: Weapons and ammo will be useful when fighting the military and bandits.

stuffs.name: Major Khaletskiy's stash
stuffs.description: A small safe is hidden in the concrete pipe. It's got some stuff I saved for a rainy day.

stuffs.name: Rookie's stash
stuffs.description: These are the things I saved for a rainy day. If it ever comes, I'll definitely come here for my supplies.

stuffs.name: Under cross on hill
stuffs.description: I hid my loot under a fake stalker grave on the hill.

stuffs.name: Chest above bridge
stuffs.description: I packed my loot in a chest at the intersection of the bridge beams. Man, I sweat a metric ton climbing up there...

stuffs.name: Pipe under felled tree
stuffs.description: We set up camp not far from the rookie village. I hid my stuff inside a pipe under the felled tree. I'll collect it later.

stuffs.name: Backpack in stovepipe
stuffs.description: Back when I was a rookie I made a little stash up in the stovepipe. I don't even remember what's in it anymore.

stuffs.name: Stash up in tree
stuffs.description: I was watching the vehicle station from a tree and decided to leave my backpack in it. The easiest way to climb there is via the branch from the side of the hill.

stuffs.name: Under locomotive
stuffs.description: My commander ordered us to help Nikolaev's group ASAP. That's when I tossed my backpack under the locomotive, next to the embankment.

stuffs.name: Backpack behind bush
stuffs.description: One night we ran into bandits and had ourselves a firefight. Not long into it we had to get our asses out of there, so I tossed my backpack in between some boulders, behind a bush.

stuffs.name: Backpack under firewood
stuffs.description: I piled some firewood up to cover my stash, which is next to a two-story building across from the farm.

stuffs.name: Cache in log
stuffs.description: I was attacked by dogs, so I didn't have much choice - I hid the loot in a cracked log in the middle of the field and ran for the camp.

stuffs.name: Hideaway in log
stuffs.description: I got hold of the coordinates of a dead stalker's hideaway - it's in a log behind the farm.

stuffs.name: Tree stump in spruce forest
stuffs.description: My buddy and I hid what little loot we had in an old stump among some fir trees.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near village
stuffs.description: I didn't walk too far to make my stash. I picked the first decent stump next to the rookie village with a hole in it. That's where I hide what I manage to find.

stuffs.name: Tree stump in woods
stuffs.description: Sidorovich asked us to make a cache next to the outpost which leads to the outside, supposedly for some rookie. I stashed everything under a tree stump near the hill.

stuffs.name: Tree stump at the Cordon
stuffs.description: On my way to the Garbage, I hid everything inside a stump in the woods so that bandits don't get nothing from me.

stuffs.name: Pipe in tunnel
stuffs.description: We were trying to hit anomalies with all kinds of trash and accidentally threw in a pipe with out loot. It's still there, collecting dust.

stuffs.name: Safe in pipe
stuffs.description: Kolyan and I made a hideaway in a safe at that junkyard near the rookie village.

stuffs.name: Safe at base
stuffs.description: Zil keeps his junk in a safe, at the neutral base at the Cordon.

stuffs.name: Green crate
stuffs.description: I saved this piece of loot specially for you. It's in the army crate on the edge of the Cordon. A piece of my heart goes with it!

stuffs.name: Small solitary backpack
stuffs.description: And so your generosity will be rewarded with magnanimity! He-he-he. Here's a stash of mine - dispose of it and its contents as you wish.

stuffs.name: Road to the Swamps
stuffs.description: I take your money, you take my stash. You'll find it along the road to the Swamps, next to a corpse.

item.name: Flash drive with data on pump mechanisms for shotguns

stuffs.name: Reward for a hero
stuffs.description: Your purchase awaits you inside the backpack next to an unlucky stalker's dead body. Look for it near the old electric locomotive.

stuffs.name: Case under train car
stuffs.description: Your "catch" is the contents of a case under a train car.

stuffs.name: Fake grave
stuffs.description: Digging up graves is wrong. But my cache is hidden in a fake one, so you won't disturb any dead people.

stuffs.name: Case behind junkyard
stuffs.description: I'll pay you with the contents of the case that is lying next to an anomaly behind the junkyard at the Cordon. There's another lad nearby reaching for it, but don't mind him - he's no longer in action.

item.name: Flash drive with data on an electronic stabilization system for shotguns

stuffs.name: Tree stump near barbed wire
stuffs.description: OK pal, to get your reward go and search a stump not far from the barbed wire

stuffs.name: Toolbox
stuffs.description: The old PDA is under the false bottom of the toolbox.

stuffs.name: Car trunk
stuffs.description: According to Stringov, the old car trunk holds some smuggler's batch of goods.

stuffs.name: Stash in anomaly
stuffs.description: If Yoga wasn't lying, a stash amidst the anomalies contains a special shooter.

stuffs.name: Electrical panel in trash
stuffs.description: I put away a little something so I could sell it at the flea market later. It's in the electrical panel next to the cabin of the fallen crane.

stuffs.name: Panel board under shed
stuffs.description: I look forward to selling this thing I got stashed inside a panel board under a shed, not far from here.

stuffs.name: Pipe at the Garbage
stuffs.description: I put my goodies inside a cut-off pipe, so that nobody could take them from me.

stuffs.name: Backpack under fir tree
stuffs.description: Until I see better days, my backpack and all its contents will stay hidden under this fir tree.

stuffs.name: Stash at junkyard
stuffs.description: I stuck my things under a concrete slab near the contaminated vehicle graveyard. I better get it back quickly, or someone beats me to it.

stuffs.name: Roof of locomotive
stuffs.description: I left my little backpack on top of the locomotive. It's easy to get to from the embankment, but not so easy to spot.

stuffs.name: Safe in puddle
stuffs.description: I doubt many people will go digging through a half-sunk safe in a puddle like that. It's a good place for a temporary stash.

stuffs.name: Safe under support
stuffs.description: I stuck my loot into a safe close to a radiation danger sign. A safecracker would have to be suicidal to try and get into it!

stuffs.name: Hole inside log
stuffs.description: I used a hole in a log not far from the concentration camp as my safe.

stuffs.name: Log behind oak tree
stuffs.description: Kolyan hooked me up with some info - he said Weedy stashes his loot in a hole in a log behind the dead oak tree.

stuffs.name: Log in bushes
stuffs.description: I stuffed my loot in a log and dragged it off into the bushes. It should stay safe and out of sight there.

stuffs.name: Lamsters' stash
stuffs.description: One of the diggers thought to get away with their loot, but Shepherd and his boys had other ideas. They wasted the dude, but couldn't find the loot. Only I saw the stump the diggers used as their stash.

stuffs.name: Solitary stash
stuffs.description: I picked a solitary hollow stump to use as a stash - just in case one of our own guys decides to rob me.

stuffs.name: Cache near base
stuffs.description: I don't know about anyone else, but I hide my stuff right under Yoga's nose - next to the fence, under an old stump.

stuffs.name: Electrical panel at junkyard
stuffs.description: The loot is under the electrical panel cover in a pile of trash.

stuffs.name: Bellmouth of pipe
stuffs.description: I made a stash in the bellmouth of a pipe, in that heap of radioactive trash.

stuffs.name: Pipe near engine
stuffs.description: Next to the dead engine at the junkyard, there's a pipe with my loot.

stuffs.name: Backpack in crane cabin
stuffs.description: I hid my backpack in the crane cabin when it was still standing up. Now I can't get in there.

stuffs.name: Hideaway from my enemies
stuffs.description: I tossed my backpack in a pile of radioactive trash so that my enemies wouldn't get it.

stuffs.name: Black backpack in wreckage
stuffs.description: What I owe you is located inside a black backpack within the wrecked construction crane.

item.name: Flash drive with data on pistol barrel modification

stuffs.name: Cut-off pipe
stuffs.description: I've got my money, but to get yours you'll have to haul ass over to this stash inside a cut-off pipe.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a pistol muzzle break

stuffs.name: Electrical panel box in wreckage
stuffs.description: Some time ago I made this stash for myself, but I'll have to give it up to you now. Oh well.

stuffs.name: Small box amidst contaminated trash
stuffs.description: I'm giving you the coordinates of a small box with loot inside. Just don't get your nuts fried - the radiation there is off the charts.

stuffs.name: Crate near bulldozer blade
stuffs.description: You'll find what you just bought at the base of a bulldozer blade.

stuffs.name: Dead man's backpack
stuffs.description: You're not afraid of ghosts, are you? Then look for a stash in the backpack next to a dead body.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a closed-cycle breathing module

stuffs.name: Corpse near excavator
stuffs.description: The lifeless lad near the flipped-over excavator will treat you to the contents of his backpack.

stuffs.name: Corpse at the Garbage
stuffs.description: Guess you'll have to sweat a little to get what I owe you. The loot's inside the backpack of this anomaly victim.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a psy-protection system

stuffs.name: En route to Agroprom
stuffs.description: Look for a small box inside the UAZ car en route to Agroprom. I think you'll appreciate the contents.

stuffs.name: Tree stump on edge of the Garbage
stuffs.description: Well, I'll give you a tip. Your compensation awaits you inside a stump on the edge of the Garbage.

stuffs.name: Electrical panel in hospital
stuffs.description: Our group made a stash in the electrical panel on the first floor of the hospital.

stuffs.name: Backpack under stairs
stuffs.description: As we were storming the second floor, we had to get rid of everything we didn't need.

stuffs.name: Barricades in hall
stuffs.description: I was in a pretty bad shootout, stuck in the hall on the hospital's second floor. Had to hid my loot in an old safe in the barricades.

stuffs.name: Habar
stuffs.description: Habar scattered around the location

stuffs.name: Habar in box
stuffs.description: Habar in box

stuffs.name: Pipe in container
stuffs.description: We got pinned down in some backyard. There was a trash container and I think I saw something in it, inside a pipe. As soon as we finish our business here, I'll go back there and check it out.

stuffs.name: Backpack by fence
stuffs.description: I was being chased, so I dropped my backpack near a fence at these coordinates.

stuffs.name: Pipe in sewer system
stuffs.description: I spotted someone's stash in the sewer pipe. I'll get it when we're back in that area.

stuffs.name: Carpetbag in attic
stuffs.description: We spent two days fighting off attacks. By the end of it, they made us retreat up to the roof, but that's when our reinforcements arrived. I spotted a case in the attic, but forgot to take it with me.

stuffs.name: Carpetbag in nook
stuffs.description: We were on our way past a backyard when I noticed a small toolbox behind the fence.

stuffs.name: Pipe under UAZ car
stuffs.description: A sack with some crap in it was sticking out from under a UAZ car. I had no time to check it out, but I might later - if I'm still alive.

stuffs.name: Behind garages
stuffs.description: I saw someone's stash behind the garages, but had no time to look through it. It's inside a large pipe behind the tree.

stuffs.name: Backpack under glove compartment
stuffs.description: I stuck poor Tin Can's backpack under the dashboard of an old Moskvich car.

stuffs.name: Dead man's backpack
stuffs.description: A rookie right next to me got nailed by a grenade - he croaked then and there. Dan took his backpack and tossed it under the bridge. A dead man has no use for it, but we might.

stuffs.name: Safe in garage
stuffs.description: We were searching the garages for a runaway and found a safe. We ought to try and crack it some time.

stuffs.name: Half-buried log
stuffs.description: Before we wasted that asshole, I saw him fiddling around that log behind the gazebo.

stuffs.name: Bundle in tree stump
stuffs.description: I saw some kind of bundle in a hole inside this stump as we were preparing for an attack.

stuffs.name: Wounded man's things
stuffs.description: They popped one into Sanek when we were climbing over a wall. He had to drop his backpack to save his butt.

stuffs.name: Stash near bunker
stuffs.description: Squint's gang was coming up on me, so I sunk a pile of loot next to some bunker hatch, in a swamp not far from the deserted vehicle station.

stuffs.name: Small box under tower
stuffs.description: I'm gathering all my loot in a stash I made under one of the high-voltage towers.

stuffs.name: Box in the cabin of ZIL car
stuffs.description: Lame Alex brought a locksmith's box from somewhere. We filled it with some goodies and stuck it into the cabin of a rusty ZIL.

stuffs.name: Pipe at station
stuffs.description: I hid something in the bellmouth of a pipe next to a valve, in the old pump station in the middle of a swamp.

stuffs.name: Backpack in the Swamps
stuffs.description: I barely escaped from one of them swamp beasts. I did drop my backpack as I was running, but I don't feel like going back there for it.

stuffs.name: Pipe in swamp
stuffs.description: I got sick and tired of lugging my stuff around and across these marshes, so I dropped it off on an peninsula, in a pipe with a valve. I figured I'd lighten my load, and the stash would be safe in those reeds.

stuffs.name: Backpack in reeds
stuffs.description: I dumped my backpack in the reed beds as I was fighting off some boars. I ain't got a reference point, just the location coordinates.

stuffs.name: Submerged safe
stuffs.description: There's a safe submerged in the water not far from the collapsed bridge. I've put all my stuff and all my trust in that stash.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near tree
stuffs.description: I decided I would stash away my loot in a tree stump next to the dry tree. I'll take it with me when I say farewell to the Swamps.

stuffs.name: Artifacts left behind
stuffs.description: I swindled some sucker and took his backpack full of loot. Then I decided to stick it in the reeds for a while so I wouldn't get caught.

stuffs.name: Grave with gas mask
stuffs.description: I trust the dead more than the living. My cache is at the graveyard, in the leftmost grave with the gas mask.

stuffs.name: Log near tower
stuffs.description: A cracked log not far from a high-voltage tower.

stuffs.name: Church woodpile
stuffs.description: Dear God, please look after my things for me. I hid them in a cracked log in the woodpile.

stuffs.name: Wooden cross
stuffs.description: I put away a little something for a rainy day. It's in the grave with the only wooden cross at the church graveyard.

stuffs.name: Safe in dirt
stuffs.description: I stuck all my loot in a safe on a swamp shore near the church. Suck it, looters!

stuffs.name: Cache in reeds
stuffs.description: I left my backpack in the reeds not far from the church. Now I can't find it, even with the exact coordinates in my PDA.

stuffs.name: Stuff in a Zaporozhets car
stuffs.description: We spent half a night on that half-sunk Zaporozhets car before our guys came to the rescue. I didn't know who'd get to us first, so I dumped my stuff somewhere around there. I oughta get there and dig it up when the sun's still shining.

stuffs.name: Carpetbag under stove
stuffs.description: What do a hot stove and a hot chick have in common? You work them long enough and you risk getting a burning sensation! Ha-ha. So, that's the kind of stove I used for hiding my carpetbag full of loot.

stuffs.name: Pipe from cistern
stuffs.description: My boys and I store our stuff in the pipe end, the one with the valve, which goes from the cistern to the Swamps.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near railroad
stuffs.description: We were passing by the railroad when we heard some shots. I ditched my things inside a stump behind some boulders, just in case.

stuffs.name: Box in kitchen
stuffs.description: I put aside some goods to trade in later, they're in a blue box in the summer kitchen.

stuffs.name: Backpack near mattress
stuffs.description: Dumbass Lekha slept on a mattress at the sunken boat, and ended up forgetting his backpack there.

stuffs.name: Stash in panel board
stuffs.description: The panel board outside the transformer room at the farmstead. Danger! Stay away!

stuffs.name: Stash in log
stuffs.description: Before I left for another part of the Swamps, I had to unload my backpack. I stuck some of my loot inside a cracked log.

stuffs.name: Electrical control unit at vehicle station
stuffs.description: When I joined Grey's gang, I put away some trinkets in the electrical control unit at the station. Who knows, it might come in useful some day.

stuffs.name: Backpack on trail
stuffs.description: I came across a monster on a trail, and all I had on me was a knife. I tossed the backpack and jumped at it. Some fellas found me later on, a mile away. I ought to go back there some time.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near young tree
stuffs.description: Let the fools be squeezed by Hook. Me, I will collect my loot little by little and stash it away under a stump near a young tree.

stuffs.name: Safe behind dead tree
stuffs.description: I'm saving loot to trade for my son's medication, stashing it away in a safe behind a dead tree. As soon as I have enough, I'll bolt to the outside.

stuffs.name: Stash in bushes
stuffs.description: I got out of the Swamps too exhausted to walk, so I dropped my stuff right on the path, in the bushes.

stuffs.name: Stash under truck bed
stuffs.description: In a toolbox under a truck, across from the bridge.

stuffs.name: In the middle of swamp
stuffs.description: I left a box of stuff in the middle of a swamp, on a piece of concrete with metal bars sticking out. I'll take it with me when I leave for the outside.

stuffs.name: Small box inside stove
stuffs.description: My stash is in a chest, the chest is in a stove, the stove is in a burned-down house, and the house is in the Swamps.

stuffs.name: Safe in reeds
stuffs.description: I don't know what a safe like that is doing here in a swamp, but I couldn't pass it up. I'll keep my stuff there for now.

stuffs.name: Tree trunk at swamp
stuffs.description: Our chief said not to take too much stuff with us. I hid mine under a stump next to the water tower, in the bushes under a tree.

stuffs.name: Sawyer in swamp
stuffs.description: I was making my way across the Swamps and noticed this rotten sawyer near a wooden deck. I thought it would make a good hideaway place for my "treasures."

stuffs.name: Backpack on island
stuffs.description: This swamp creature kept chasing me all over the place. After a few miles of that marathon, I got so tired that I had to drop my backpack at one of the islands.

stuffs.name: Hatch near station
stuffs.description: I buried my goodies under one of the hatches near the station, just so I wouldn't lose it all to some robber.

stuffs.name: Cache in pipe
stuffs.description: That black backpack in the big pipe is all that's left of Mitka.

stuffs.name: Toolbox in cabin
stuffs.description: I found a toolbox in a swamp, put all my stuff in it and hid it in a crane cabin. I'll wait until things get better before I make use of it.

stuffs.name: Backpack under train car
stuffs.description: I was trying to get away, so I lightened my load by dropping off my backpack under a train car on the railway bed.

stuffs.name: On the ledge of dome
stuffs.description: I left my backpack on the ledge of the church dome. I must have looked like a wild goat hopping around on that roof.

stuffs.name: Under bridge
stuffs.description: We hid under a bridge while the guys chasing us ran across it. I left my backpack with some loot down there, next to a beam.

stuffs.name: Between boulders
stuffs.description: I tossed my bag in a crack between three boulders, or else I would look like a target to some greedy fellas.

stuffs.name: Sawyer under boulders
stuffs.description: I kept searching for a safe place for my stash and found a nice sawyer with a hole in it under some boulders in the reeds.

stuffs.name: Backpack on corpse
stuffs.description: Here's a stash tip for you: it's in the backpack on the back of a corpse.

item.name: Flash drive with data on a submachine gun muzzle break

stuffs.name: Paratrooper
stuffs.description: You'll find the stiff at these coordinates - his backpack holds what you're due.

stuffs.name: Extra hassle
stuffs.description: Go an extra mile, find the dead soldier's backpack - and you'll get your expenses back with interest.

stuffs.name: Fighter's corpse
stuffs.description: Here's the info: a young figher "resting" in the bushes is guarding his backpack for you.

stuffs.name: Backpack under pipeline
stuffs.description: Take these coordinates - they point to a backpack next to a stalker's corpse under the pipeline.

stuffs.name: Backpack as payment
stuffs.description: The contents of this backpack, whose coordinates I'm uploading to your PDA, are more than worth the cash you're depositing into my pockets.

stuffs.name: Code-locked safe
stuffs.description: Your payment is well worth the loot hidden in this safe at the Swamps.

stuffs.name: Loot as payment
stuffs.description: The loot you'll find in the black backpack under the boulders is now yours. Let's consider this transaction settled.

stuffs.name: Small crate at tower
stuffs.description: A trusted source once told me about some loot in a no man's stash hidden under a tower.

stuffs.name: Cache on Swamps
stuffs.description: There's a very valuable cache at the recycling factory at the Swamps. Whatever its contents, now they're yours.

stuffs.name: Safe with reward
stuffs.description: Dude, these keys open a safe that holds something valuable. Or so I'm told...

stuffs.name: Reward
stuffs.description: Our secret stashes for your money. Selling them all down the river to you alone.

stuffs.name: Small case
stuffs.description: In that case, here are the coordinates of a case with some loot. You'll find it behind the trash bin, near the wall.

stuffs.name: Safe under bridge
stuffs.description: I won't burden you with my stories. You'll find the stash in the safe under the bridge.

stuffs.name: Dear soldier's backpack
stuffs.description: You'll get quite a bit more than what you paid. Your reward is inside a backpack next to a soldier's corpse.

stuffs.name: Tough reward
stuffs.description: I will reward you with information about a valuable but "tough" piece of loot. Keep on your toes though - its previous owner failed to heed my advice...

stuffs.name: Military warehouse
stuffs.description: No data

stuffs.description: Ammo crate

stuffs.name: Case in stove
stuffs.description: I stuck a small case inside a stove in a dilapidated hut. I'll be stashing my goodies there as I collect them.

stuffs.name: Backpack near chimney
stuffs.description: I left my backpack next to a chimney in the attic of a dilapidated house. I'd go back if it weren't for that bloodsucker in the village.

stuffs.name: Backpack under trailer
stuffs.description: I saw this one dude throw his backpack under a trailer right before an emission hit. I ought to go check it out.

stuffs.name: Stash under bridge
stuffs.description: Backpack is in a train car under the bridge in the army base.

stuffs.name: Crack in tunnel
stuffs.description: I dropped my backpack in the crack above the tunnel when the "heat" started, but it got caught on a metal bar. It was a shame to leave without it - I really ought to go back and get it.

stuffs.name: Stash in toilet
stuffs.description: I doubt anyone's gonna look for a stash in the village toilet. But that's where mine is, so I ain't worried about it.

stuffs.name: Cache near fence
stuffs.description: I dropped off poor Kolyan's backpack behind the hangar. I had enough of my own stuff to carry.

stuffs.name: Backpack under tree
stuffs.description: The second I saw that monster next to the water tower, I dropped my backpack under a fallen tree like a hot potato. Times like that running light can save your life.

stuffs.name: Cracked tree log
stuffs.description: I hid my stuff in a log under a pine tree, next to the fallen tower.

stuffs.name: Tree stump behind concrete slabs
stuffs.description: A stump in between two boulders, behind a pile of concrete slabs.

stuffs.name: Stash in grave
stuffs.description: I buried my stuff under a grave cross. Let it rest in peace until I come back for it.

stuffs.name: Cross near tree
stuffs.description: I made a stash in the grave next to a tree.

stuffs.name: Pipe at base entrance
stuffs.description: I hid my stuff under the ensign's very nose. It's inside the pipe behind the watchman's booth, at the entrance to the base.

stuffs.name: Stash in Moskvich car
stuffs.description: When Max returns, I'll give him his backpack. Meanwhile let it stay in that old Moskvich.

stuffs.name: Backpack in basement
stuffs.description: I was so dizzy after the emission that I dumped my backpack in a basement. I'll come back for it after I get back on my feet.

stuffs.name: Forgotten backpack
stuffs.description: An explosion smashed a wall to bits and a piece of it trapped me under. I had to drop my backpack to climb outta there and kick some ass, and that was so much fun I ended up forgetting all about the backpack. Probably still down there...

stuffs.name: Cache in kitchen
stuffs.description: A green backpack in the kitchen stove in one of the houses of the deserted village. Coordinates recorded.

stuffs.name: Stash under boulder
stuffs.description: I was hauling ass the other day, and I left a backpack full of hot goods in the bushes between two boulders.

stuffs.name: Stash in peasant's sled
stuffs.description: Stash in huge log next to peasant's sled.

stuffs.name: Log under boulders
stuffs.description: At the very edge of some boulders there's a log, and inside it, away from prying eyes, is my cache.

stuffs.name: Stump next to fence
stuffs.description: Vityok said he left my share of the loot in the hole of a tree stump that's between the military base's fence and the small swamp.

stuffs.name: Backpack under dead body
stuffs.description: It may not be a real stash, but there should be some valuable loot in that backpack on the water tower.

stuffs.name: Cache under uprooted tree
stuffs.description: Take it from me - there's a cache under the uprooted tree.

stuffs.name: Grandma's safe
stuffs.description: I don't know how a safe got on that stove, but my sources say it's not empty.

stuffs.name: Grave stash
stuffs.description: There's word that you can get rich if you look under the cross at these coordinates.

stuffs.name: Crate at military base
stuffs.description: If you manage to sneak into the military base, you'll find a reward for your troubles in a crate in an attic.

stuffs.name: Safe in closet
stuffs.description: My sources tell me something is kept in the safe at the military barracks.

stuffs.name: Small safe
stuffs.description: Captain Yeltyshev carried this safe with him all the time, until he got transferred to another location. Why don't you check it out and see what's inside?

stuffs.name: Pile of trash
stuffs.description: Java stuck his stuff in a pile of trash on purpose, only he later forgot about it. I made a note though, and now I'm passing it on to you.

stuffs.name: Box with secret
stuffs.description: Behind the cabin of the army MAZ there's a small box with a secret. That's the secret I'm selling you.

stuffs.name: Stash in woods
stuffs.description: A backpack is hidden under the rocks in the woods, and I'm passing its coordinates to a good man.

stuffs.name: Habar
stuffs.description: Habar scattered around the location

stuffs.name: Habar
stuffs.description: Habar scattered around the location

stuffs.name: Habar
stuffs.description: Habar scattered around the location

stuffs.name: Pipe in cart
stuffs.description: I stuck my things inside a pipe and tossed it into a rusty cart at the old quarry.

stuffs.name: Blue crate
stuffs.description: My loot's in a blue crate on the second floor of the building near the caper.

stuffs.name: Backpack in bushes
stuffs.description: We were making our way through the bushes, and I somehow managed to lose my backpack.

stuffs.name: Things inside tree hole
stuffs.description: On the way to Limansk me and Whip hid our stuff in the hole of a felled tree, near the exit from the reserve.

stuffs.name: Hole-laden tree stump
stuffs.description: I heard screaming and howling, so I put my things inside the nearest hole-laden tree stump and split.

stuffs.name: Tree stump in front of forest
stuffs.description: We don't know what awaits us in this forest...so we've hidden our extras in a rotten stump.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near ravine
stuffs.description: We put our stuff away near that helluva an anomaly. Our target is the anomaly itself. It's so amazing that it's bound to contain some real valuable artifacts.

stuffs.name: Black backpack
stuffs.description: Crap, I lost my black backpack when I was running out of the forest. I even know where it is, but I ain't going back there unless they napalm the whole damn place to hell.

stuffs.name: Backpack on tree branch
stuffs.description: I hid from some monster up in a tree. I didn't see the beast itself, but I heard it all right. I left the backpack on the branch, jumped off and ran for my life.

stuffs.name: Tree next to fence
stuffs.description: A damn bloodsucker chased me all the way to the reserve fence and up a tree. If I hadn't left my backpack in that tree, I would never have made the jump to the fence.

stuffs.name: Boulder near ravine
stuffs.description: Several dogs cornered me next to a ravine, so I tossed my backpack into some boulders and tried to break through.

stuffs.name: Backpack in forest
stuffs.description: That was like being inside a horror movie. I don't know how I got out...Lost my backpack, but I remember there was only one place where I could have dropped it.

stuffs.name: Backpack under boulders
stuffs.description: Kolya's backpack was too much to carry, so I placed it under some boulders at the exit to the Limansk bridge.

stuffs.name: Cursed loot
stuffs.description: That backpack's got quite a story! All the guys who handled it are dead. I threw it away to never see the cursed thing again.

stuffs.name: Weird place
stuffs.description: I dozed off next to a boulder, lying on my backpack. Come morning, I found myself in an entirely different place. I tried to find that boulder, but something just kept me going in circles.

stuffs.name: Backpack under rockslide
stuffs.description: Some boulders broke loose from the ravine and fell right on me at the exit from the Red Forest. Then something dark started to reach out to me from behind them. I barely made it out, but had no choice but to drop my stuff along the way.

stuffs.name: Lost backpack
stuffs.description: That idiot Abe lost my backpack in some rocks, somewhere around this spot. Now he's too afraid to go back and get it. A true friend, indeed!

stuffs.name: Stash in mine gallery
stuffs.description: I hid my artifacts at the very end of a deserted mine gallery.

stuffs.name: Backpack in cave
stuffs.description: I crawled inside a cave at night to get some sleep. I got a rude awakening from a bloodsucker tugging on my bag. I split from there like a track champion, but the bloodsucker's still got my backpack.

stuffs.name: Large tree stump
stuffs.description: Seva told me about a large hollow stump in the Red Forest. I'll try to locate it and see what's inside.

stuffs.name: Stash in stump
stuffs.description: Gene and I hid a few things in a stump in the Red Forest.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near ravine
stuffs.description: I hit this stump as I was falling into the ravine, so I hid my loot in it for the time being.

stuffs.name: Stump in the wilderness
stuffs.description: I got lost in the Red Forest and dropped all my junk right here, inside a hole in a stump.

stuffs.name: Dead stalker
stuffs.description: I saw in a dead stalker's PDA that his backpack contained something of interest. Here are those coordinates.

stuffs.name: Dangerous stash
stuffs.description: I already pointed some chump to this stash, but I know he never got to it - he kicked the bucket in an anomaly close by.

stuffs.name: Red valve
stuffs.description: The stash is hidden behind the red valve of the mine pipe system. Its contents do not interest me in the least.

stuffs.name: Bus
stuffs.description: A friend of mine made his stash under the backseat of this bus. He's no longer with us, so he won't mind if you raid his little hiding place.

stuffs.name: Pipe in rubble
stuffs.description: I learned about this hideaway from a prisoner - it's in a piece of pipe in the rubble behind the APC.

stuffs.name: Crate with backpack
stuffs.description: Your treasure is simply fabulous! OK, take note - the reward's in the backpack, backpack's in the crate, crate's at the bridge, bridge's on the other side of the Red Forest.

stuffs.name: Poor guy's backpack
stuffs.description: This poor bastard was bringing me a backpack through the Red Forest, but never made it. If you find it, it's all yours.

stuffs.name: Safe near trolley car
stuffs.description: My info is all true and no bullshit. Some hobo hid something valuable in a safe near the flipped-over trolley car.

stuffs.name: Ordinary old tree stump
stuffs.description: There's a cache in the hole-laden stump. Nothing special, just an inconspicuous place you won't find without my coordinates. That's why I'm giving them to you.

stuffs.name: Pipe in mine
stuffs.description: I know for sure there's something valuable in this stash in the Red Forest.

stuffs.name: Electrical box at the factory
stuffs.description: I looked into Andrey's PDA and saw that when the "brain grinder" started to come down, he made a stash in a rusty electrical box at the factory.

stuffs.name: Panel board inside the transformer room
stuffs.description: When the whole factory started to cut out, I dumped all my stuff inside the panel in the transformer room.

stuffs.name: Case at the factory
stuffs.description: I was at the hangar when I found what used to be a toolkit. It was rattling, but I had no time to look inside - just left it there until next time.

stuffs.name: A small case in the truck
stuffs.description: A nice place for a cache - right in between the cab and the truck bed. The local zombies and radiation make for good natural protection.

stuffs.name: Stash next to the fence
stuffs.description: I hid a little something at the intersection of pipes near the construction car, next to the fence.

stuffs.name: A few trinkets inside a pipe
stuffs.description: I took the most valuable stuff with me and put the rest inside a pipe in the room with a hole in the wall.

stuffs.name: Backpack near the entrance
stuffs.description: I had to leave a full backpack of loot in the ruins right next to the entrance. I wonder if someone's discovered it yet...

stuffs.name: Cache in the ventilation duct
stuffs.description: Hey, Tony, remember the coordinates and the reference point - the backpack is inside the ventilation duct next to the broken-through wall of the compound. Regards, Owl.

stuffs.name: Backpack under the seat
stuffs.description: I had no time to think, so I stuck my loot under the driver's seat in the rusty UAZ vehicle.

stuffs.name: Stash in the crane gear box
stuffs.description: God only knows what made me go and make my stash all the way up there. Now even I can't reach it!

stuffs.name: Cache in the safe
stuffs.description: The best cache in the Zone belongs to me. It's a safe on the factory premises.

stuffs.name: Hollow log
stuffs.description: I hid my stuff in a hollow log next to the "thorn."

stuffs.name: Log near the hill
stuffs.description: With those zombies coming from the factory, I had no choice but to part with my loot. I hid it in a log at the foot of the hill.

stuffs.name: Tree stump near the tower
stuffs.description: I set up another stash in the hole of a stump, on that hill with the high-voltage tower. Everybody thinks I go there for the view, dumbasses!

stuffs.name: Log behind garages
stuffs.description: I hid my bit of loot in a log near the garages, next to the Yantar factory. Best place I could find at the time.

stuffs.name: Crate on the roof of boiler room
stuffs.description: There's a small hideaway inside a blue crate on the roof of a boiler room. The area is teeming with zombies, so watch out.

stuffs.name: Crate in train car
stuffs.description: Great - now take these coordinates of a crate inside the train car at the factory. Go there and you'll know what to do.

stuffs.name: Backpack by drain pipe
stuffs.description: Find this backpack by the drain pipe and we'll be even. There's a dead neutral lying nearby, so you'll spot this place easily.

stuffs.name: Case at the scientists' base
stuffs.description: Excellent! Take everything you find inside the crate in the trunk of a UAZ in the scientists' base.

stuffs.name: Booth with switchboard
stuffs.description: I'll reimburse you with the coordinates of a cache in the booth near the factory.

stuffs.name: Cistern bellmouth
stuffs.description: Something is hidden in the cistern bellmouth at the factory. I never checked out what exactly.

stuffs.name: MAZ truck cabin
stuffs.description: You'll find the stuff in the cabin of this MAZ truck, packed into a case.

stuffs.name: Corpse in lake
stuffs.description: Look for the backpack of this soldier who's taking a leisurely swim in the lake.

stuffs.name: Tree stump across from scientists' camp
stuffs.description: Look for the hideaway under the stump across from the scientists' camp.
